You are not ill, Raymond.  You are suffering from some ancient conditioning called PTSD.  It is long standing, but still it is a &quot;condition.&quot;  It is not a mental illness.. but it feels like it.  Emotions have a way of wiping out our smarts sometimes.  There is a lot to learn about PTSD that can help you.  The clinical stuff is helpful or harmful.. depends upon who you link up with.<br>
I would recomend that you gain some knowledge about:<br><br>
1.  Triggering stimuli...What sets you off!<br>
2.  The relation between Affect and Cognition.. or simply thoughts and emotions.<br>
3.  In depth look at fear and control.<br>
4.  Rejection and acceptance.<br>
5.  Unreasonable guilt.<br>
6.  Low self esteem.<br>
7.  Why Marines wear funny looking uniforms.<br>
8.  How high altitude flying causes jet jockies to lose brain cells due to oxygen debt. <br>
9.  Why infantrymen think ashpalt is a disease of the butt.<br>
10. Why helicopter pilots are so gifted at anything and everything.... being the studs that they are!<br><br>
. ....and Most of all... why you are so important to all of us here on this site.<br><br>
We talk some heavy stuff.. get sad.. get pissed.. get serious and get a lot of mutual admiration.<br>
Feel free to e-mail me for serious issues or just jump right in with the rest of us.<br><br>
Welcome Home.. God Bless.. 
